So basically this is a project to create a post with image and caption and date
also to show the post whatever we make....so basically we are gonna create a post and ue get to view then


npm init -y
npm i express

Step 1: Create a server in app.js
        -Add a middleware and require all the packages and files line by line while working
Step 2: Create a server . js file 
      - to start the created server
      -after that check if the server is working or not

Note: Export each and every file so that they can be used in other files i.e server.js or any other by using require

Step 3: Decide what apis and data and how, where and in what format we should store the data
Step 4: Lets start with the database and connect it to server
      -Create a db folder and a db.js file in the src folder
      -This file is for database connection and configuration in mongodb or any other database platform
      -Require the database like mongoose in the file to use it
      -make an async function and connect mongo cluster to it by its url and give it /data_name
      -Now export the function

Step 5:  create a model folder in src folder and in it create a post.model.js file where we can store the schema and model of the data
      -schema is a blueprint for the data that we want to store in the database. It defines the structure of the data and the type of data that we want to store.
      -model is a class that we can use to create documents in the database and perform operations on them
      -create a function for schema and models
      -export models

Step 6: The api creating part with differt methods...........and here we are using get and post method

Step 7: First create a post method in app.js file to send the files and raw data to the cloud storage service from where we can access it afterwards
      -here we create a multer middleware by installing npm i multer and require it
      -upload.single is a middleware function from multer to handle file uploads, it expects the name of the file input field as an argument, in this case "image"

Step 8 is to create a service folder where we can operate the cloud storage service
      - 1st provide the private and public key in an instance
      -then write a function according to the documentation of the cloud server to upload files to it
      -export the function